{"questionId":"22263371","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of scalar product formula to find angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>∙</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>use of cosine rule to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1417</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92405</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If the direction of one of the vectors is reversed, leading to an obtuse angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>124</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>858</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math> between the vectors, then award <em><strong>M1A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22263371","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the size of BA^D. the area of triangle BAD.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Vector definitions","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar and vector products"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}